The paper deals with a MIMO system with low-resolution ADCs, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed approach uses coding theory to transform a non-linear MIMO channel to a linear MIMO channel, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also proposes efficient MIMO detection methods using algebraic coding theory, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
